@SUPERCOW  

Remand is definitely more versatile as you can use it to bounce one of your own spells gone wrong or force your opponent to discard on a full hand. [Memory Lapse](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Memory Lapse) has versatility in a mill deck but Remand does so much more on its own. Also, the fact that it cantrips means you aren't losing card advantage by playing it and gives it value if you're just trying to stall out the game until you get that one card you badly need. (Something I've had first hand experience with many times.)  

Memory Lapse is an amazing card and impacts the opponent more. If you have a deck that builds around it, or a deck with something that Memory Lapse builds around itself, then yes, it can be much more devastating. But Remand is just waaay too handy to overlook in any deck that uses counter magic.
